<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Anyone curious what interviews are like can get an idea from the office hours we've done at TC Disrupt and Startup School.  Interviews are similar, but with more questions (partly because there are more of us asking them, and partly because we need to arrive at a decision, not just have a conversation).<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2011/05/25/absolute-must-watch-office-hours-with-paul-graham-at-tc-disrupt/" rel="nofollow">http://techcrunch.com/2011/05/25/absolute-must-watch-office-...</a><p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2011/09/12/tc-disrupt-office-hours-with-yc-partners-paul-graham-and-harj-taggar/" rel="nofollow">http://techcrunch.com/2011/09/12/tc-disrupt-office-hours-wit...</a><p><a href="http://www.justin.tv/startupschool/b/298808297" rel="nofollow">http://www.justin.tv/startupschool/b/298808297</a></font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=40></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3198815 href="vote?for=3198815&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%47%4e%72%4e%4f%4c%31%4a%47%45"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3198815></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=hristov">hristov</a> 91 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3198815">link</a></span></div><br>
<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>You might be interested to know that the German guy you instructed to launch immediately back in September has not launched yet.<p>But I should not be too sarcastic. I really liked these. A lot of the interviewees were very promising even after your well meaning attempts to shoot holes in their business models. And your comments are very informative.<p>But it seems that your comments and questions also indicate how hard it is to build a successful start-up. It is not merely about making something useful or better than the competition, you have to make something that cures a significant pain point so that your customers are actually motivated to go out and get it. It really does make one take a pause and question things.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=40></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3197902 href="vote?for=3197902&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%47%4e%72%4e%4f%4c%31%4a%47%45"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3197902></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=collint">collint</a> 92 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3197902">link</a></span></div><br>
